beer.beer_description:
Crafted with Galaxy hops, Kosciuszko Pale Ale delivers a fruity take on the Australian pale ale style. It refreshes your palate with pleasant rich malt and a fruity hoppy finish.

Kosciuszko Pale Ale was inspired by the Snowy Mountains. Polish explorer Edmund Strzelecki, the first to ascend Australia's highest mountain 1840, named it in honour of the Polish freedom Fighter Kosciuszko.

Malt: Pale Ale and Speciality Malt

Hops: Galaxy

Yeast: Australian Ale
